description: Thousands of migrants sleep rough on the island of Lesbos after fire engulfs their squalid camp.
title: Moria migrants: Greek ships to help shelter 13,000 after fire
title_page: Moria migrants: Greek ships to help shelter 13,000 after fire - BBC News
maintext: One woman from Afghanistan held her baby girl, born 25 days ago. She said she and her family had spent the night out in the open, as the police had not let them return to Moria. She said no one had brought them either food or water.
